\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 5.               Christella}                   Léveillé
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By A.C. Jermy & A.M. Paul.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Rhizome creeping. Leaves 1-pinnate, with pinnatifid pinnae, hairy; veins free except for the lowermost pair of each segment, which unite with those from the adjacent segments to form a single vein, excurrent in the sinus. Sori orbicular, medial; indusium reniform, densely hairy; spores papillose, the papillae often confluent to form ridges. ({\i Cyclosorus} Link.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b 1. C. dentata} (Forskål) Brownsey & Jermy,{\i  Brit. Fern Gaz.}{\b  10:} 338 (1973) ({\i Cyclosorus dentatus} (Forskål) R.-C. Ching,{\i  Dryopteris dentata} (Forskål) C. Chr.,{\i  D. mollis} (Jacq.) Hieron.,{\i  Aspidium molle} (Jacq.) Swartz). Rhizome stout, the apex covered with shiny brown, lanceolate, hairy scales. Leaves 30-100 cm, forming a crown at the apex of the rhizome, pinnate; petiole less than 1/3 as long as the lamina, light brown, hairy; lamina lanceolate to elliptical, tapering abruptly at the apex; lower pinnae often very reduced in size; longest pinnae 10-15 × 1-2 cm, pinnatifid; segments parallel-sided, truncate at the apex, sparsely hairy above, densely hairy beneath. Sporangial stalks glandular.{\i  Damp places beside streams. Açores; Mediterranean region, very local}. Az Cr Hs ?It Si. ({\i Old World tropics}.)
