\pard\f0\fs28 Rhizome short, erect or occasionally creeping, with dark, linear-triangular to linear-lanceolate, sometimes filiform scales. Leaves in apical tufts; petiole dark, at least at the base, often glabrous; lamina entire or variously dissected; veins free or rarely marginally anastomosing. Sori elliptical to linear; indusium resembling the sorus in shape and size, attached along the vein, sometimes rudimentary or absent.
\par

